T|22 ·|0|The "software factory": a portfolio of coding projects plus a Kanban of coding tasks, run by Nexus (CTO) w/ a mandatory Steve (QA) gate. Nexus can cr PRs and dp but can never merge to main — the owner reviews.
T|22 ·|1|
T|Purp|0|Where actual software gets built. Nexus is connected to the GitHub repo and to vc, can dp, and is only allowed to cr PRs — never merge to main. Every piece Nexus codes passes a qual-assurance stage w/ Steve before reaching the owner's rv. This page has two layers: a portfolio overview and a task Kanban.
T|Purp|1|
X|Laye|0|Title: Software Pipeline, breadcrumb Vibe w/ AI / Software Pipeline.
X|Laye|1|Top stats: pd (e.g. 5), shipped this XX, shipped this week, active tasks (e.g. 44).
X|Laye|2|Buttons: Portfolio, Board / List toggle, Search & filter.
X|Laye|3|Project cards — one per pd, each w/ status and progress:
X|Laye|4|Idea-Feed MVP — needs you / "X needs rv" badge, progress %, "X in progress / X stage."
X|Laye|5|By ds — "X needs work," progress.
X|Laye|6|Canela Shop — "X in progress," discount/feature note, progress.
X|Laye|7|Mission Control — the dashboard itself, "X needs work," progress.
X|Laye|8|Valhalla Tools — "Active," progress.
X|Laye|9|Each card links to GitHub / vc and shows active task counts.
X|Laye|10|
K|Laye|0|A board of coding tasks w/ stages tuned to the Nexus→Steve→owner flow:
K|Laye|1|
K|Laye|2|TRIAGE — incoming tasks to be sorted (e.g. "Onboarding tooltip overlaps w/ shortcut," "Fix cart badge count on tap one mobile").
K|Laye|3|PLANNING — scoped/spec'd tasks (e.g. "Stream counter on the home lab · X subtasks," "Decision-queue keyboard shortcuts").
K|Laye|4|BACKLOG — approved, not started (e.g. "Stream counter on the home lab · X subtasks").
K|Laye|5|IN PROGRESS — Nexus actively coding (e.g. "Apple sign-in flow," "Shopify webhook retry").
K|Laye|6|STEVE QA — Steve's qual-assurance gate: checks the code aligns w/ the task/spec. If anything's off, it goes back into Planning (re-picked by Nexus). Example: "Brain search relevance tuning," "Venue CSV import validation."
K|Laye|7|NEEDS rv (human gate) — passed QA, now awaiting the owner's rv (e.g. "Voice-memo intake → structured idea"). Escalates into the Decision Queue / merge gate.
K|Laye|8|DONE — merged/shipped (e.g. "Push notification opt-in," "Discount-code field at checkout").
K|Laye|9|
K|Laye|10|A filter row across the top: All pd / By ds / Canela Shop / Idea-Feed MVP / Mission Control / Valhalla Tools, plus "Awaiting my rv · Stuck > 3 days" quick filters.
K|Laye|11|
K|Righ|0|Selecting a NEEDS rv task opens a detail panel, e.g. "Voice-memo intake → structured idea · Needs you":
K|Righ|1|A description of what was built and a short demo/preview (a player thumbnail — "record a voice memo, get a clean structured idea card w/ title, summary, and suggested nx step. Is this what you want?").
K|Righ|2|Two-stage gate recap: ✓ Steve QA — tests pass, QA green, acceptance met → Your final rv — does it work & feel right? ap / send back.
K|Righ|3|Compose / nudge actions and a PRD / Mockup reference (links to the spec and the mock).
K|Righ|4|Actions: Open PR, ap, or send back.
K|Righ|5|
D|Agen|0|Nexus (CTO): writes code, opens PRs, deploys to vc — never merges to main.
D|Agen|1|Steve (QA): independent qual gate btw Nexus and the owner; failed checks loop back to Planning.
D|Agen|2|Owner: final reviewer/merger for the projects Nexus codes.
D|Agen|3|Connected to GitHub (repo/PRs) and vc (deploys).
D|Agen|4|
T|Work|0|Idea Feed → project in portfolio → task: Triage → Planning → Backlog → In Progress (Nexus) → Steve QA → Needs rv (owner) → Done. QA failures return to Planning; owner-rv items also surface in the Decision Queue.